CRITICS' CHOICE: LIAR'S POKER: RISING THROUGH THE WRECKAGE ON WALL STREET BY 
MICHAEL M. LEWIS (W. W. NORTON: $15.95; 265 PP.) 
"Despite its iconoclastic tone, the book is an informative insider's 
description of the peculiar macho culture of investment bankers. . . a sort of 
pilgrim's progress through the land of avarice." Scot J. Paltrow 
